Use the web_fetch tool to retrieve the content of a web page by URL. Provide a full URL starting with http:// or https://. The tool strips HTML and returns plain text. You can optionally specify max_chars to limit the response length. Use this when the user asks you to read or summarize a web page, or when you need to look up information from a specific URL. Always include a link back to the source URL in your response so the user can visit the original page.